      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <fig class="- topic/fig ">
               <image href="../Images/powerblockprinciplediagram_120mm_0000116662.svg"
                      scalefit="yes"
                      translate="yes"
                      xml:lang="en"
                      placement="inline"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">One power module consists of:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">3 rectifiers (PFC and step-up)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">3 inverters</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">1 battery charger (step down)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">1 RFI board</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">1 PSU board</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">1 current limiter and filter board</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Three individual rectifiers and three individual inverters
form one power module with a 20 kVA rating. Each PFC rectifier and
inverter is connected in one common single phase board. For a 3-phase
output configuration each line (phase) has its own board. For a 1-phase
output configuration the three boards are in parallel and the 120°
phase shift is disabled.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">3-Phase Output System</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">One power module consists
of three individual inverters each of which deliver 6.7 kVA with a
phase shift of 120°. In a 3-phase configuration with one power
module (20 kVA System), the individual output line delivers 6.7 kVA.</p>
         <fig class="- topic/fig ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">One power module in a 3-phase output configuration</title>
            <image href="../Images/powermoduleconfig_120mm_0000116660.svg"
                   scalefit="yes"
                   translate="yes"
                   xml:lang="en"
                   placement="inline"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">1-Phase Output System</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">In a 1-phase output
system, the three individual phases are connected and the 120°
phase shift for each phase is disabled. The system rating is 20 kVA.</p>
         <fig class="- topic/fig ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">One power module in a 1-phase output configuration</title>
